"'''Horning In'''" is a mini-adventure for any era, published on the [[Wizards of the Coast]] website. It was written by [[Jeff Quick]] and published in [[2001]]. The adventure introduces a search for the [[Quadronomic Fluxer]].

==Publisher's summary==
"Horning In" is a [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]] adventure for four 10th-level heroes of any persuasion. The adventure's set in the [[Rebellion era]], but it can be modified easily to work in any other era of play as well. Although the villain of the story flies a ship described in ''[[Starships of the Galaxy]]'' and the scenario calls for a [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ship]] that also could be taken from the pages of that accessory, the book isn't required to run this adventure.

The rumor mill has been grinding out stories lately about a new fuel mixture component for [[Sublight engine/Legends|sublight drives]] called a [[Quadronomic Fluxer]]. If rumors are to be believed, Fluxers can improve sublight speed by as much as 20 percent. Both the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] would be willing to risk a lot to find out if it's legitimate -- and to keep it out of the hands of the other group. That's where the heroes come in.

The plans for the Fluxer are hidden within a [[Shipyard/Legends|shipyard]] orbiting the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Nessem]], in the [[Expansion Region/Legends|Expansion Region]] of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. Either as agents of the Rebellion or on their own, the heroes must travel to the main station of the [[Nessem Shipyards]], hook up with an undercover contact there, and retrieve the plans. But they'd better take care - if the Quadronomic Fluxer is real, it just might be a secret worth killing for .

